Mr Olusegun Osinaike has assumed office as the newly-appointed Tutor-General/Permanent Secretary of the Lagos State Education District IV. This was disclosed in a statement issued by the state government and made available to newsmen on Tuesday. The statement quoted Osinaike as, during a welcome party, promising to develop the district, declaring his readiness to work with the management and other members of staff towards achieving his mandate and the actualisation of the T.H.E.M.E.S development agenda of the state government. Thanking Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu for appointing him out of many others who are equally qualified, Osinaike said, “I will put in my best to make sure the district has the best WAEC and BECE results throughout my tenure in office.” He also thanked the workforce for the reception while soliciting their support and collaboration to achieve all set goals and objectives of the Education District IV. The welcome party was led by the district’s Director, School Administration Department, Mr Akeem Amosu, who commended Sanwo-Olu for his leadership style and for providing an enabling environment for teachers and learners in the state to thrive. He congratulated Osinaike, assuring him of the full support and cooperation of the entire management and staff members in taking the Lagos State Education District IV to an enviable height. He implored the Permanent Secretary to consider himself and other members of staff as one family while praying for the success of the district.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com